dcterms:description: The effective exposure time variable represents the depth (i.e., quality) of the images collected, indicating the level of brightness required for detecting the faintest point source at a given reference signal-to-noise ratio.
dcterms:title: Effective exposure time (tef f ective)

dcterms:description: An offline dataset containing examples of interactions between the Stone Edge Observatory telescope and the sky, generated through a simulation tool. It consists of 309,599 observations representing state-action-reward-next state samples.
dcterms:title: Stone Edge Observatory (SEO) offline dataset
